  "text": "6 The TFP growth of Latin American countries after 1990 lagged significantly the performance prior to 1980 [CITATION_1] . This suggests, at the very least, that the import-substitution policies of the past were able to produce respectable efficiency gains overall. 7 Chile's export industries in agriculture (grapes, wine), forestry, and fisheries (salmon) have all benefited greatly from government support in the form of subsidies and public R&D.",
